  "signature": "ed25519:b7e3a1f4c9d2e6b8a5f1c3d7e9b4a2f6c8e1d5b9a3f7c2e4d6b8a1f5c9e3d7b2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/sqa-level2",
      "rationale": "FEA software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) is commercial, FDA-recognized, and operated under a documented SQA plan including version control, regression test suite, and change management records. All three ensemble solvers passed SQA audit prior to use. Achieved Gradation 2 satisfies the required level for a Medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/code-verification-level2",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and ASME V&V 10 were solved using the same element formulations (SOLID186 hexahedral) and solver settings as the pedicle screw model. Results matched analytical solutions to within 0.5% for linear elastic beam bending and contact patch problems. Code verification is documented in the FEA verification report (rev. C)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/discretization-level2",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.5 mm, fine 0.3 mm global element size) was performed on the screw-rod assembly. Richardson extrapolation yielded a grid convergence index (GCI) of 0.8% for construct stiffness and 1.1% for yield force on the medium mesh selected for production runs. Discretization error is formally bounded and below the 2% threshold defined in the acceptance criteria, exceeding the required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/solver-error-level1",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver residuals were monitored for all load steps; force residual norm converged below 1e-4 and displacement residual below 1e-5 for every increment. Iterative solver (PCG with incomplete Cholesky preconditioner) tolerance set to 1e-8. No unconverged increments were recorded across the ensemble of 11 simulation replicas. Achieved level exceeds the required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/use-error-level2",
      "rationale": "Model setup followed a documented simulation protocol reviewed by two independent analysts. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were verified by a second reviewer against the protocol checklist before each production run. Peer review sign-off records are archived. No deviations from protocol were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-form-level2",
      "rationale": "The FEA model uses continuum solid elements with bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity for Ti-6Al-4V (ASTM F136), Hertzian-regularized surface-to-surface contact at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces, and rigid body constraints at grip fixtures consistent with ASTM F1717 test setup geometry. Model form assumptions are documented and justified against published literature on metallic implant FEA (Patel et al. 2018, Izzo et al. 2020)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/model-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa, n = 0.05) were sourced from certified material test reports for the production lot used in bench testing. Geometric dimensions were measured from CMM scans of three production screws; variability was below 0.02 mm for all critical dimensions. Torque preload on set screws was measured and applied as an equivalent prestress. Input uncertainty was propagated via Latin Hypercube Sampling (n=200) confirming QoI sensitivity dominated by yield strength, which was directly measured."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-samples-level2",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes R&D). All constructs were manufactured from the same production lot, with certificate of conformance and dimensional inspection records available. Sample size provides sufficient statistical power (>80%) to detect a 10% difference in mean stiffness at α=0.05."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single loading condition (static compression-bending per ASTM F1717 at a single crosshead displacement rate of 5 mm/min, ambient temperature). While this matches the intended COU exactly, only one test condition was explored and no parametric variation of rate, temperature, or fixture geometry was performed. This limits the factor to Gradation 1, which is below the required level of 2. This known gap is documented and accepted given that the COU is restricted to the single standardized test condition, and the decision consequence is Medium rather than High."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/equivalency-inputs-level2",
      "rationale": "A one-to-one mapping table was constructed between FEA model inputs and experimentally measured parameters. Material properties, geometry, boundary conditions, and loading were each traced to a specific measured value from the physical test specimens. No surrogate or assumed values were used where direct measurements were available. The mapping was reviewed and approved by the independent credibility assessment team."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/output-comparison-level2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison used the ASME V&V 10.1 validation metric E/u_val for all three QoIs. Stiffness: E/u_val = 0.84 (|%diff| = 3.2%); Yield force: E/u_val = 1.21 (|%diff| = 5.7%); Force at 40 mm: E/u_val = 1.38 (|%diff| = 6.9%). All three metrics satisfy E/u_val < 1.96 and |%diff| < 10% acceptance bounds. Uncertainty in validation metric includes experimental measurement uncertainty (Type A and B), model parameter uncertainty from LHS propagation, and numerical solution error. Full uncertainty budget is documented in the UQ report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary biomechanical performance metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to the regulatory decision regarding structural adequacy of the pedicle screw construct. These QoIs are the same quantities used in predicate device comparisons and are clinically meaningful indicators of construct integrity under physiological-equivalent loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/criteria/validation-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the COU: the same device geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), the same loading protocol (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), the same material lot, and the same FEA modeling framework are used in both the validation and the intended regulatory submission context. No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is required for the COU decision. The validation is therefore directly applicable without interpolation or domain-transfer assumptions."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment finds that the FEA model ensemble meets the overall Medium assurance level required for a Class II device with Medium model influence and Medium decision consequence. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors achieve their required credibility levels. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is accepted based on two considerations: (1) the COU is explicitly restricted to the single standardized ASTM F1717 static compression-bending condition, so no extrapolation beyond the validated domain is performed; and (2) the quantitative validation metrics for all three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/u_val < 1.96, |%diff| < 10%) with margin, providing direct empirical evidence of model adequacy under the specific condition of use. The provenance chain from foundational material test data through FEA predictions to experimental comparison is complete and documented. The decision is Accepted with the condition that any extension of the model to additional loading conditions or screw geometries requires reassessment of the Test conditions factor and a new credibility evaluation.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
